"WMP and Media Center are unfortunately the only programs (thus far) I've found to work this way; I would hope that future versions of Windows Live Photo Gallery make similar changes.With the addition of Libraries, Windows users now have a large proportion of the functionality that was promised with the (long-cancelled) WinFS"
"Once upon a time, WinFS would have been a database-based filesystem, which would provide, amongst other things, fast searching, virtualized folders that grouped content according to its type, and an extension of these features to non-local storage"
"Through Windows Search and Libraries we now have these same abilitiesâ€”only without the immense technical complexity that undermined WinFS"
"With the addition of file synchronizationâ€”a feature provided by Live Meshâ€”almost every capability of WinFS is now available.Device Stage was also shown off at PDC, and is part of a broader overhaul of how devices attached to the system are exposed to the user"
